    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A 2018 Toyota Camry with a P0171 code, indicating a system too lean on bank 1, can be a bit tricky, but let's tackle it with a few more steps. First, check the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor again, as it can sometimes be the culprit despite appearing fine. Next, ensure that the fuel injectors are not clogged or leaking. A clogged injector can cause a lean condition. Also, check the oxygen sensors and the fuel pressure regulator. A faulty oxygen sensor or a malfunctioning fuel pressure regulator can lead to improper air-fuel mixture. If all these components seem fine, you might want to consider getting a professional diagnostic to rule out any hidden issues. Remember, a lean condition can be quite dangerous, so it's best to handle it with care.",
      "source": "target",
